      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Coastal, Jungles, Rivers</em></p>\\n<p>Calamus is a reed that grows in grassy clumps, reaching 2â€“6 feet tall. It has small yellow-green flowers and long, thin, light-green leaves with a faintly sweet scent. The root, white with a reddish-brown peel, must be peeled and boiled in fresh water within a day of harvest; the resulting decoction is drunk. If no permanent damage exists to a person's hearing, a dose may restore a small portion of hearing (roughly 10% of normal) and grants +1 to Perception checks involving sound for those with functional hearing. Folklore also attributes aphrodisiac properties to the herb (DM's discretion), and some ancient tribes reportedly used it to make dogs more aggressive (DM's discretion).</p>",
